<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-12-09T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-12-09T18:00:00-05:00" n="877" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d877">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/2178a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Representative on Special Mission in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Crowder</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-12-09T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">December 9,
                                        1921—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>185. The Government of Cuba has expressed desire that the Marines should
                            be withdrawn from the Province of Camaguey. Please cable whether in your
                            opinion their presence there is still necessary.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>